Features

🔥 Friction Score

Instead of compatibility score:

“Potential Arguments Per Week”

Examples:

* 2/10 = “Probably roommates.”
* 8/10 = “Will either marry or destroy each other.”

⸻

🧲 Opposite Magnet

Pairs based on weird contrasts:

* sleep schedule
* hobbies
* music
* personality
* lifestyle

But filters for:

* shared values
* safety
* kindness
* actual dealbreakers

So it’s chaotic — not reckless.

⸻

🎭 First Date Roulette

Suggested dates intentionally outside both comfort zones.

Examples:

* pottery class
* monster truck rally
* wine tasting
* medieval combat show
* bird watching
* axe throwing

⸻

📉 Red Flag Marketplace

Users openly list:

* annoying habits
* irrational opinions
* toxic traits they’re working on

Examples:

“Will absolutely steal your fries.”

“Thinks every movie is too long.”

“Owns tactical equipment for no reason.”

Honesty becomes funny and humanizing instead of performative.

⸻

Secret Sauce

The algorithm isn’t really matching opposites.

It’s matching:

* complementary energies
* curiosity gradients
* narrative tension
* psychological novelty
* shared humor bandwidth

People often don’t actually want clones of themselves.

They want:

* expansion
* surprise
* movement
* polarity with safety

